###1800s (unknown year), southern NSW###
The black looked wild and frightened; and, in sad soliloquy, said, "Bell cooleen, bell pater, 
these poor fellas, all tumble down when euroka jump up :-- nothing to eat, nothing to drink, 
these poor fellas will all die when the sun jumps up." Graham (1863:278) 
Written in Ireland on the basis of the author’s returned eldest brother’s tales of over twenty years in Australia 
(Graham 1880:86-7).
